bed9f9a3-e639-4faf-b16f-3972c1a476e2.4b4f4c5b-e3b3-4ef7-926f-ee890c841348.prompt=Enter user bed9f9a3-e639-4faf-b16f-3972c1a476e2.4ddbc349-f6e3-4b16-9620-1534c4e8db4c.description=
Clone a virtual machine. The virtual machine may be a template vm. The source virtual machine is specified via vmIdentifierType and virtualMachine (optionally vmDatacenter) while the target configuration is defined by vmName,vmFolder,vmResourcePool,dataStore,hostSystem, and clusterName.

Note\: cannot work across virtual datacenters

Inputs\:
host - VMWare host hostname or IP
user - VMWare username
password - VMWare user's password
port - Port to connect on
protocol - Connection protocol (http or https)
closeSession - Close the internally kept VMWare Infrastructure API session at completion of operation?
virtualMachine - Primary Virtual Machine identifier. IP (IPv4 or IPv6 depending upon ESX version), hostname (full), inventorypath (Datacenter/vm/MyResourcePool/MyVM), UUID, or the VM id (vm-123,123)
vmIdentifierType - Virtual machine identifier type
async - Asynchronously perform the task
taskTimeOut - Time to wait before the operation is considered to have failed (seconds)
vmDatacenter - Virtual machine's datacenter
vmName - Virtual machine name being created (new)
vmFolder - Virtual machine's folder by inventory path, / delimited not including datacenter (eg. ManagedVMs/DRS/Location1). For root folder, use /
vmResourcePool - Virtual machine's resource pool
dataStore - Datastore (eg. host\:dsname, mydatastore)
hostSystem - Target virtual machine host system
clusterName - Name of the VMWare HA or DRS cluster
markAsTemplate - Mark the virtual machine as a template? Mark as regular virtual machine otherwise
customizationTemplateName - Customization template name to use on the existing virtual machine or on the newly created one if a new VM is being created.

Responses\:
success - The operation completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.

Returns\:
returnResult - Task result or operation result.

Notes\:
Inventory Path Formatting\: If host is an ESX server inventory path will be\: ha-datacenter/vm/ .  If host is a vCenter or vSphere server the inventory path will be\: /vm// . The / part of the path is based on the "Virtual Machines & Templates" view in the vCenter or vSphere client. The inventory path is case sensitive.

vmIdentifierType - Virtual machine identifier type
vmPowerState - Virtual machine power state to set (poweredOn, poweredOff, suspended).

Responses\:

failure - Something went wrong.
no action - The operation completed with no action performed.

Returns\:

Notes\:
Inventory Path Formatting\: If host is an ESX server inventory path will be\: ha-datacenter/vm/ .  If host is a vCenter or vSphere server the inventory path will be\: /vm// . The / part of the path is based on the "Virtual Machines & Templates" view in the vCenter or vSphere client. The inventory path is case sensitive.
bed9f9a3-e639-4faf-b16f-3972c1a476e2.600c68df-039b-40ec-9484-dc03679aacda.prompt=Virtual Machine name\: bed9f9a3-e639-4faf-b16f-3972c1a476e2.66bb5e6c-6327-45ba-85a3-a828d4cb8675.prompt=Virtual Machine\: bed9f9a3-e639-4faf-b16f-3972c1a476e2.6f8444f2-960a-4fde-b84e-072e393399ce.prompt=dataStore bed9f9a3-e639-4faf-b16f-3972c1a476e2.74781750-5cef-490e-8393-3f60f9e79041.description=
 Apply a guest customization spec to an existing VM.

Inputs\:
    host - VMWare vCenter hostname or IP.
    user - VMWare username.
    password - VMWare user's password.
    port - Port to connect on.
    protocol - Connection protocol.
Valid values\: "https", "http"
    closeSession - Close the internally kept VMWare Infrastructure API session at completion of operation.
Valid values\: "true", "false"
    async - Asynchronously perform the task.
Valid values\: "true", "false"
    taskTimeOut - Time to wait before the operation is considered to have failed (seconds).
    vmIdentifierType - Virtual machine identifier type (inventorypath, name, ip, hostname, uuid, vmid).
    virtualMachine - Primary Virtual Machine identifier. Inventorypath (Datacenter/vm/Folder/MyVM), Name of VM, IP (IPv4 or IPv6 depending upon ESX version), hostname (full), UUID, or the VM id (vm-123,123).
    vmDatacenter - Virtual machine's datacenter.
    customizationTemplateName - Name of the customization specification to apply to the virtual machine. The customization specification should already exist in the vCenter customization specifications manager. This is not a required input. However, if  both 'customizationTemplateName' and 'customizationSpecXml' are empty or have input, the operation will give an error message and fail. Hence, either 'customizationTemplateName' or 'customizationSpecXml' should have an input.
    customizationSpecXml - The Xml string of the customization spec to apply. This is not a required input.

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed successfully.
    failure - Something went wrong.

Returns\:
    returnResult - Operation result message.

Notes\:
1>Inventory Path Formatting\: If host is an ESX server inventory path will be\: ha-datacenter/vm/ .  If host is a vCenter the inventory path will be\: /vm// . The / part of the path is based on the "Virtual Machines & Templates" view in the vCenter client. The inventory path is case sensitive.

2>Guest customization spec can be applied only to a vm.

3>If the operation fails due to "A customization operation is pending on the vm\: ", then restart the guest of the vm before applying a different customization specification.

4>The result of the VMware/VMware Virtual Infrastructure and vSphere/Guest/Export Guest Customization Spec operation can be used to get the customizationSpecXml input value.

5>If the Microsoft Sysprep Tools for a particular windows guest operating system is not already bundled with the vCenter Server then it must be installed on the vCenter Server system. For instructions on Guest Operating System Customization Requirements see "Customizing Guest Operating Systems" on page-42 in http\://www.vmware.com/pdf/vsphere4/r41/vsp_41_vm_admin_guide.pdf
bed9f9a3-e639-4faf-b16f-3972c1a476e2.8eda7314-d97c-45ce-b459-3c91a4912c92.prompt=addDiskSize bed9f9a3-e639-4faf-b16f-3972c1a476e2.907e3778-de22-4d88-8804-51e525b78082.description=
Retrieve information about a virtual machine or a group of virtual machines in a datacenter or host system (pipe-delimited). Retrieve each object one at a time from an initial search query ala SQL Query operation.

Inputs\:
host - VMWare host hostname or IP.
user - VMWare username.
password - VMWare user's password.
port - Port to connect on.
protocol - Connection protocol (http or https).
closeSession - Close the internally kept VMWare Infrastructure API session at completion of operation?
vmDatacenter - Virtual machine's datacenter.
vmIdentifierType - Virtual machine identifier type.
hostSystem - Target virtual machine host system.
virtualMachine - Primary Virtual Machine identifier. IP (IPv4 or IPv6 depending upon ESX version), hostname (full), inventorypath (Datacenter/vm/MyResourcePool/MyVM), UUID, or the VM id (vm-123,123).
getDetailed - Retrieve detailed information?

Responses\:
success - The operation completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.
no more - there are no more results to retrieve.

Returns\:
vmInfo - Virtual machine information.
numberOfResults - Number of results from the query remaining to be retrieved.
returnResult - Virtual machine ID or operation results.

Notes\:
Inventory Path Formatting\: If host is an ESX server inventory path will be\: ha-datacenter/vm/ .  If host is a vCenter or vSphere server the inventory path will be\: /vm// . The / part of the path is based on the "Virtual Machines & Templates" view in the vCenter or vSphere client. The inventory path is case sensitive.
bed9f9a3-e639-4faf-b16f-3972c1a476e2.94aa9c61-6755-42d7-b533-c0788b9ce121.prompt=Enter password bed9f9a3-e639-4faf-b16f-3972c1a476e2.ad3a6df3-0999-4bb3-8498-04a413aa7642.prompt=extendDiskSize bed9f9a3-e639-4faf-b16f-3972c1a476e2.bbaa9c76-69b8-48c3-a997-99a060eb8bd3.prompt=vmDatacenter bed9f9a3-e639-4faf-b16f-3972c1a476e2.c05575b7-84a3-40d7-b5f9-35af4f2727ec.prompt=user bed9f9a3-e639-4faf-b16f-3972c1a476e2.description=
Create a VM from a VM template. Must specify either hostSystem, clusterName, or vmResourcePool as a target location for VMs.

This flow is copied from CSA/3.x/Providers/vCenter/vCenter Clone Server/Subflows, and make necessary changes according to PC's requirements.
Changes - Add input customizationSpecXml

Input Parameters\:
 vmName - name of the VM that will be created with this flow
 templateName -  name of the VM template to clone in vCenter
 osType - linux or windows
 host -  vCenter host to execute against
 user - vCenter username
 password - vCenter password
 vmDatacenter -  target Datacenter on the vCenter host for the VMs
 dataStore -  target datastore on the vCenter host for the VMs
 hostSystem - target ESX host for the VMs
 clusterName - target cluster for the VMs
 vmResourcePool - target resource pool for the VMs
 CPUs - Number of cpus to be set on the VMs
 Memory - Amount of Memory in MB to be set on VMs. Memory should be a multiple of 4.
 port - Port Number toconnect on
 protocol - Connection prtocol(http, https)
 availableCPU - Available CPU in  vCenter
 availableMemory - Available Memory in MB in vCenter


Responses\:
 success - The operation completed successfully.
 failure - Something went wrong.
   

Result Fields\:
 vmId - VMID of the Clone
